heading: Temple of Kalabsha (New Kalabsha, Egypt).
alt-heading: Mandulis, Osiris, and Isis, Temple of (New Kalabsha, Egypt).
Temple of Mandulis, Osiris, and Isis (New Kalabsha, Egypt).
general-note: Here are entered works on the temple built during Roman times at Kalabsha, Egypt, that was dismantled in 1962 and reassembled at a higher site south of the new Aswan Dam.  Works on a small Ptolemaic chapel that was built into the Roman Temple of Kalabsha and revealed when that structure was dismantled and that was reconstructed on Elephantine Island are entered under. Sanctuary of Kalabsha (Elephantine, Egypt)..
